[0.663, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;163H9\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.543, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;164H^M\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H      \u001b[1;2H most of the above items can be used here (apart from radio interface specific\u001b[2;3Hitems, like channel)\u001b[29X\u001b[4;2Hbss=wlan0_1\u001b[59X\u001b[5;2Hbssid=00:13:10:95:fe:0b\u001b[53X\u001b[6;3H...\u001b[72X\u001b[7;2H\u001b[24X\r\n# Multiple BSSID Advertisement in IEEE 802.11ax\r\n# IEEE Std 802.11ax-2021 added a feature where instead of multiple interfaces\u001b[10;3Hon a common radio transmitting individual Beacon frames, those interfaces can\u001b[11;3Hform a set with a common Beacon frame transmitted for all. The interface\u001b[12;3Hwhich is brought up first is called the transmitting profile of the MBSSID\u001b[13;3Hset which transmits the Beacon frames. The remaining interfaces are called\u001b[14;3Hthe non-transmitting profiles and these are advertised inside the Multiple\u001b[15;3HBSSID element in the Beacon and Probe Response frames from the first\u001b[16;2H interface.\u001b[17;2H\u001b[74X\u001b[18;3HThe transmitting interface is visible to all stations in the vicinity, however\u001b[19;3Hthe stations that do not support parsing of the Multiple BSSID element will\u001b[20;3Hnot be able to connect to the non-transmitting interfaces.\u001b[21;2H\u001b[10X\r\n# Enhanced Multiple BSSID Advertisements (EMA)\u001b[23;3HWhen enabled, the non-transmitting interfaces are split into multiple\u001b[24;3HBeacon frames. The number of Beacon frames required to cover all the\u001b[25;3Hnon-transmitting profiles is called the profile periodicity.\u001b[15X\u001b[26;2H\u001b[39X\u001b[27;3HRefer to IEEE Std 802.11-2020 for details regarding the procedure and\r\n# required MAC address assignment.\u001b[29;2H\u001b[65X\u001b[30;3HFollowing configuration is per radio.\r\n# 0 = Disabled (default)\u001b[32;3H1 = Multiple BSSID advertisement enabled.\u001b[33;2H 2 = Enhanced multiple BSSID advertisement enabled.\u001b[34;2Hmbssid=0\u001b[60X\u001b[35;2H\u001b[13X\n The transmitting interface should be added with the 'interface' option while\u001b[37;3Hthe non-transmitting interfaces should be added using the 'bss' option.\u001b[38;3HSecurity configuration should be added separately per interface, if required.\u001b[39;2H\u001b[24X\u001b[40;3HExample:\u001b[15X\u001b[41;2Hmbssid=2\u001b[11X\u001b[42;2Hinterface=wlan2 \u001b[43;2Hctrl_interface=/run/hostapd   \u001b[44;2Hwpa_passphrase=0123456789\u001b[45;2Hieee80211w=2\u001b[46;2Hsae_pwe=1\u001b[33X\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f3340,1         99%\r\u001b[24A\u001b[?25h"]
